Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{220%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%g} and bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%min}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{12-15%mins} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{10%g}, @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} and half the garlic.

Next, add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs onto a large #baking tray{}.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop into 1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%mins} total. Turn only every couple of mins.

Once cooked, season with salt and pepper, then transfer the courgette to a bowl.

Pop the (now empty) pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{} (no need to clean).

Add the remaining garlic to the pan and fry for ~{30%secs}. Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chermoula spice mix{1%sachet}, @water{100%ml}, a @?sugar{pinch} and the remaining chicken stock paste.

> Add less chermoula spice mix if you'd prefer things milder.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once the meatballs are cooked, stir them into the spiced sauce along with the charred courgette.

Cook until piping hot, ~{1%min}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Remove from the heat.

Share the bulgur out between your bowls and top with the chermoula meatballs and courgette to finish. Enjoy!